{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"42cce430-8a32-40f1-a739-718877c45df2","content":"Here's the recommended MSTest setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` brings in MSTest, the runner, and CodeCoverage automatically. No `<PackageReference>` items needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution (`.runsettings`)\n\nCreate a `.runsettings` file at the project root:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>  <!-- 0 = use all available cores -->\n      <Scope>MethodLevel</Scope>\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nOr use the assembly-level attribute approach in a file like `AssemblyInfo.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 0, Scope = ExecutionScope.Method)]\n```\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` ensures that class runs alone — no other tests execute concurrently with it.\n- You can apply it to individual `[TestMethod]`s too if only some methods need isolation.\n- Workers `0` means \"match processor count\" for maximum parallelism everywhere else.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a45df49a-119a-4167-b489-7eaf34bdb969","outputTokens":470,"requestId":"843C:37AAD:21B68D8:254B891:6A0AD44C"},"id":"e16518cc-7e95-4465-8ca8-2bae9b0c3b4e","timestamp":"2026-05-18T08:57:00.952Z","parentId":"605105c7-7fd9-464a-a085-b0df193e6fec"}
